cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper focuses on computer vision tasks such as person and vehicle re-identification, which are commonly studied in the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The paper also proposes a method for feature aggregation, which involves training a Siamese network, indicating a possible fit for the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper introduces a new dataset for vehicle re-identification, suggesting a potential fit for the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. The paper also involves training a neural network, indicating a possible fit for the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves evaluating the performance of the proposed method, which could fit into the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category.
